<promed@promedmail.org>
[Previously it was suggested that the suspected outbreak on Easter Island
may have originated with the arrival of tourists (or an infected mosquito)
from Tahiti in January. Consequently the strain of dengue virus responsible
for the outbreak may be distinct from the strains (and serotypes) of dengue
virus presently circulating in Latin America and the Caribbean. It is
possible, however, that virus arrived earlier with the first appearance of
the vector on Easter Island. ProMED-mail would welcome information on
characterization of the Easter Island virus. - Mod.CP
